<TITLE> Policeman arrested on charge of taking bribe </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 5 (bdnews24.com) - The Detective Branch (DB) of Police have arrested a sub-inspector of Motijheel Police Station in the city on charges of taking bribe. The detectives arrested Ali Hossain from a club at Motijheel at about 8pm Thursday after a case was filed against him by assistant manager of Prime Insurance Co Ltd's Kamal Pasha. Duty officer of Motijheel Police Station sub inspector Kibria said Kamal alleged that he filed a case with the police station in July in connection with two lost cars of the company. Ali was the investigating the case, but as there had been no progress in the investigation after three months. On Wednesday night Ali took Tk 10,000 in bribe from Kamal on the pretext that it was needed if the investigation was to made any headway. bdnews
